Popular American actor Will Smith has emerged as Best Actor at the 75th British Academy of Film Awards (BAFTA). He emerged a winner for his role in a biographical drama film ‘King Richard’. The awards were presented on Sunday at an in-person event in London’s Royal Albert Hall, London.   ‘Portable needs rehab not shows’     Nigerian comedians can sell out 02 arena – Kenny Blaq     American actor William Hurt dies at 71   Actress Joanna Scanlan floored American singer-turned-actress Lady Gaga to emerge the leading actress. Five awards were also won by the sci-fi film ‘Dune’ while the Western drama ‘The Power of the Dog’ directed by Jane Campion, won the best film.